The error we fixed was related to the resource identifier in the ErSambuconeGUI class. Minecraft requires resource identifiers to use only lowercase letters, numbers, forward slashes, periods, underscores, and hyphens. The original code was using uppercase letters in the path (`ErSambuconeGUI.html`), which caused the crash.

Our solution was to:
1. Change the resource identifier in the code to use lowercase letters (`ersambucone_gui.html`)
2. Rename the actual HTML file to match the new lowercase name

